Now, I will warn you; if you don’t like digging into your food, cracking shells with your hands and getting a little messy, this is NOT the place for you.  Otherwise, get ready for a fantastic feast!! The menu leads you through the process; it’s something like this: 1. Pick your meat 2. Pick your sauce 3. Pick your spice level  We got the lobster combo with white & red sauce-no spice.  They bring you a bucket, bibs, and gloves and your table is covered in parchment paper. Then when your food is ready, they bring it out in bags and dump it on your table 😂😂 And you get Crackin’!!  So yummy 😋  My only regret was that we weren’t able to do the sweet art afterwards (dessert). They called it that and they were not exaggerating. They bring out these colorful sauces and create a wonderful piece of art on the clean parchment paper, and then give you donuts and fruit to wipe it up. A table near us got it, so I was able to see it, but being Gluten Free it didn’t make sense for us to get it. Definitely neat to watch though-how innovative!!  I highly, highly recommend the Crackin’ Kitchen; it’s a fun experience and delicious dining all at one time.
